# generate-demo-doc for Cursor

Use `generate-demo-doc/PROMPT.md` as the shared instruction source and
`generate-demo-doc/references/demo-template.md` as the template.

When the user requests a demo document:

- Accept a PR URL, PR number, Jira URL, or Jira key.
- Build context in this order: Jira, PR, local repo docs.
- Write the result as a business-facing internal demo document, not a changelog.
- If Feishu publishing tools exist in the current setup, publish and verify by title search.
- If publishing tools do not exist, return the markdown document and clearly note that publishing was skipped.
